With Boris Johnson on the way out as Britain’s prime minister, what happens next? The Economist’s editor-in-chief discusses the latest developments in Westminster with Andrew Palmer (Britain editor), Matthew Holehouse (British political correspondent) and Duncan Robinson (Bagehot columnist). As the Conservative Party’s leadership contest gets under way, they consider the country’s chaotic political climate, Mr Johnson’s legacy, and what it all means for Britain, Europe and the wider world.  Visit our subscriber events page to view the schedule for our forthcoming events. Subscribers can also watch recordings of all our previous sessions.